{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4e21d23b-8320-4ce0-a87b-07f318fce7ca","content":"Here's guidance on evaluation format and best practices for MCP tool evaluations:\n\n## Format: `evaluation.yml`\n\nEvaluations are typically defined in YAML. Each entry has a **natural-language question** and **expected outcomes** (tool calls, argument values, or answer content). Example structure:\n\n```yaml\nevaluations:\n  - name: search_by_category\n    question: \"Find all products in the 'Electronics' category under $50\"\n    expected_tool_calls:\n      - tool: search_products\n        arguments:\n          category: \"Electronics\"\n          max_price: 50\n    expected_answer_contains:\n      - \"Electronics\"\n\n  - name: product_detail_lookup\n    question: \"What is the warranty period for product SKU-4821?\"\n    expected_tool_calls:\n      - tool: get_product_details\n        arguments:\n          sku: \"SKU-4821\"\n```\n\n## What Makes a Good Evaluation Question\n\n| Principle | Example |\n|---|---|\n| **Test correct tool selection** — ask something only one tool can answer | *\"How many items are in the 'Shoes' category?\"* (should pick `count_products`, not `search_products`) |\n| **Test argument extraction** — embed specific values the LLM must parse | *\"Find red sneakers between $40 and $80 sorted by rating\"* |\n| **Test multi-step reasoning** — require chaining two+ tool calls | *\"Compare the prices of SKU-100 and SKU-200\"* (two `get_product_details` calls) |\n| **Test ambiguity handling** — see if the LLM clarifies or picks a reasonable default | *\"Show me the cheapest laptop\"* (must infer category + sort) |\n| **Test negative cases** — the answer isn't in the data | *\"Is there a product called 'Quantum Toaster'?\"* |\n\n## Tips\n\n- **Start with golden-path cases** — one tool, obvious arguments.\n- **Add edge cases** — missing optional params, empty results, boundary values.\n- **Keep questions realistic** — phrase them how a real user woul